00:21:16,292 --> 00:21:17,790
CCTVs?

272
00:21:17,793 --> 00:21:20,090
But it was three months ago. The records must be gone.

273
00:21:20,095 --> 00:21:22,685
What else can we do? Let's give it a try.

274
00:21:22,831 --> 00:21:24,900
There must be private surveillance cameras...

275
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,700
in the stores and buildings nearby.

276
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:29,700
Are you saying you want me to hack all those cameras?

277
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:33,170
If that helps us catch the criminal, it will be worth it.

278
00:21:33,175 --> 00:21:35,970
Check the CCTVs near the road.

279
00:21:35,978 --> 00:21:38,235
I'll check if there are more cameras.

280
00:21:39,815 --> 00:21:42,405
Seriously, this is nothing but a waste of time.

281
00:21:45,287 --> 00:21:49,745
Gosh, you'd better pay me well for this.

282
00:22:39,475 --> 00:22:41,695
(Won Suk)

283
00:22:49,118 --> 00:22:51,235
Okay.

284
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:07,655
(Won Suk)

285
00:23:09,671 --> 00:23:11,870
Why are there so many cameras?

286
00:23:11,874 --> 00:23:13,425
Darn it.

287
00:23:13,609 --> 00:23:15,270
Gi Mu Hyeok, that brat.

288
00:23:15,277 --> 00:23:18,435
Where is this? Goodness.

289
00:23:20,149 --> 00:23:23,650
- Hello, sir. - Good morning.

290
00:23:23,652 --> 00:23:24,680
- Hello, sir. - Hi.

291
00:23:24,686 --> 00:23:27,280
- Hello, sir. - Hello.

292
00:23:27,289 --> 00:23:29,820
Nice. Morning.

293
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:31,890
- Hello, sir. - Hi. Good.

294
00:23:31,894 --> 00:23:34,790
Could you smile a bit?

295
00:23:34,797 --> 00:23:36,690
- Hello, sir. - Hi.

296
00:23:36,698 --> 00:23:38,700
- Hello, sir. - Hello.

297
00:23:38,700 --> 00:23:41,700
Are you two dating again? Focus on your study.

298
00:23:41,703 --> 00:23:43,970
- Hello, sir. - Hi. Keep it up.

299
00:23:43,972 --> 00:23:47,640
Let's work hard. Move.

300
00:23:47,643 --> 00:23:50,395
Let's kick Butler Lee out.

301
00:23:52,281 --> 00:23:54,550
He doesn't suit our school.

302
00:23:54,550 --> 00:23:56,280
He's been always bothering me.

303
00:23:56,285 --> 00:23:59,150
And he even created a scene at Tae Ra's recital.

304
00:23:59,154 --> 00:24:01,645
Kicking him out won't be enough.

305
00:24:01,790 --> 00:24:04,445
We must destroy him.

306
00:24:13,402 --> 00:24:15,425
Why do I still see them?

307
00:24:15,637 --> 00:24:18,340
I told you to delete all of them.

308
00:24:18,340 --> 00:24:19,400
Once I make my debut,

309
00:24:19,408 --> 00:24:22,140
I will make you the president of my fan club or whatever you want.

310
00:24:22,144 --> 00:24:24,880
Ye Ri, you'd better ask a digital undertaker...

311
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:27,680
rather than me.

312
00:24:27,683 --> 00:24:29,880
I want to have a normal life again.

313
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:32,180
I can't let them handle that.

314
00:24:32,187 --> 00:24:34,875
I'm almost a celebrity.

315
00:24:34,923 --> 00:24:36,605
"Celebrity"?

316
00:24:38,727 --> 00:24:40,790
I couldn't do my job because I had to help you.

317
00:24:40,796 --> 00:24:42,660
And now I'm about to be fired.

318
00:24:42,664 --> 00:24:45,515
Could you please set me free now?

319
00:24:46,602 --> 00:24:50,755
Or how about you snitch on him?

320
00:24:51,773 --> 00:24:53,425
Snitch?

321
00:24:54,042 --> 00:24:55,040
How?

322
00:24:55,043 --> 00:24:56,870
What do you mean by, "how"?

323
00:24:56,879 --> 00:24:59,380
You said there's something fishy about that man.

324
00:24:59,381 --> 00:25:01,310
Can't you just snitch on him to a reporter or something...

325
00:25:01,316 --> 00:25:03,605
and kick him out?

326
00:25:36,985 --> 00:25:40,775
Can we talk?

327
00:25:41,890 --> 00:25:43,405
Sure.

328
00:26:03,345 --> 00:26:04,965
Ms. Ha.

329
00:26:05,180 --> 00:26:08,535
Where are we going now?

330
00:26:09,284 --> 00:26:13,635
Somewhere you must go at least once.

331
00:26:15,090 --> 00:26:17,975
And we have to take a taxi to get there?

332
00:26:30,505 --> 00:26:32,325
(Prosecution Service)

333
00:26:35,477 --> 00:26:38,980
Hey, what's up? You never call me out.

334
00:26:38,981 --> 00:26:40,810
How about a cup of coffee?

335
00:26:40,816 --> 00:26:42,705
Coffee is nice here.

336
00:26:46,855 --> 00:26:48,290
Are you out of your mind?

337
00:26:48,290 --> 00:26:49,945
Seriously.

338
00:26:50,092 --> 00:26:51,460
Why are you so shocked?

339
00:26:51,460 --> 00:26:53,560
I'm telling a prosecutor about corruption.

340
00:26:53,562 --> 00:26:55,085
Hey, you...

341
00:26:57,966 --> 00:27:00,200
You want to rat out Mr. Yang, your direct superior?

342
00:27:00,202 --> 00:27:03,070
Even if he's my superior, he must be punished if he commits a crime.

343
00:27:03,071 --> 00:27:04,800
You'll get fired first.

344
00:27:04,806 --> 00:27:06,455
And Mr. Yang is...

345
00:27:07,342 --> 00:27:10,210
He got there with no skills because of his connections.

346
00:27:10,212 --> 00:27:12,740
He has connections at the Supreme Prosecutors' Office too.

347
00:27:12,748 --> 00:27:15,610
Look. I'll worry about that.

348
00:27:15,617 --> 00:27:19,075
You just do your job as the prosecutor of Insection Department.

349
00:27:19,488 --> 00:27:22,745
Are you serious? I'm losing my mind here.

350
00:27:23,892 --> 00:27:26,760
It's not my fault if something happens to you.

351
00:27:26,762 --> 00:27:29,690
No one will take in a prosecutor who rats out a superior.

352
00:27:29,698 --> 00:27:31,185
You know that, right?

353
00:27:33,568 --> 00:27:34,800
Thanks.

354
00:27:34,803 --> 00:27:37,755
It's nice to have a friend who worries about me.

355
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:41,155
Thanks for this. See you.

356
00:27:42,811 --> 00:27:44,265
Hey...

357
00:27:47,616 --> 00:27:49,505
Get out, you jerks!

358
00:27:50,085 --> 00:27:51,820
Stop that.

359
00:27:51,820 --> 00:27:53,805
Where is it?

360
00:27:53,955 --> 00:27:55,850
I don't have it! I mean it!

361
00:27:55,857 --> 00:27:58,920
Where is the money?

362
00:27:58,927 --> 00:27:59,990
Here it is!

363
00:27:59,995 --> 00:28:01,645
Stay still.

364
00:28:07,202 --> 00:28:10,655
You're really making me mad.

365
00:28:11,106 --> 00:28:14,470
- You have money, but you... - Don't hit him.

366
00:28:14,476 --> 00:28:18,465
What? Why don't you wave a knife at us like last time?

367
00:28:19,481 --> 00:28:22,735
You audacious little twerp.

368
00:28:22,851 --> 00:28:24,480
Do you want to die?

369
00:28:24,486 --> 00:28:26,035
Stay still.

370
00:28:33,095 --> 00:28:34,545
What's this?

371
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:37,285
Beom Jin.

372
00:28:38,233 --> 00:28:39,715
Is he your friend?

373
00:28:42,204 --> 00:28:44,985
That's right. He's my friend.

374
00:28:45,006 --> 00:28:46,595
He is?

375
00:28:47,209 --> 00:28:48,610
That's good.

376
00:28:48,610 --> 00:28:52,295
Friends are supposed to help each other in times of need.

377
00:28:54,182 --> 00:28:56,450
You're decked out in designer clothes.

378
00:28:56,451 --> 00:28:59,050
If we strip you now, that will be enough...

379
00:28:59,054 --> 00:29:01,105
to pay your friend's interest.

380
00:29:02,624 --> 00:29:04,945
Will you give me your business card?

381
00:29:05,093 --> 00:29:06,590
Really?

382
00:29:06,595 --> 00:29:08,990
Really? You want to pay?

383
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:11,045
Here it is, our new client.

384
00:29:11,967 --> 00:29:13,755
(Youth Loans)

385
00:29:15,637 --> 00:29:17,400
(Youth Loans)

386
00:29:17,405 --> 00:29:20,425
What a great friend.

387
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:29,980
(Help me)

388
00:29:29,985 --> 00:29:31,535
What...

389
00:29:34,055 --> 00:29:36,105
What are you doing?

390
00:29:37,459 --> 00:29:39,590
I requested help with the police.

391
00:29:39,594 --> 00:29:42,390
I said I'm being held hostage in your office and asked for help.

392
00:29:42,397 --> 00:29:44,145
What? Hostage?

393
00:29:44,733 --> 00:29:46,585
You brat.

394
00:29:51,072 --> 00:29:52,895
That must be a confirmation call.

395
00:29:52,908 --> 00:29:54,455
What should I do?

396
00:29:55,010 --> 00:29:57,395
They'll think I'm really being held hostage if I don't answer.

397
00:29:57,712 --> 00:30:00,195
You crazy little punk.

398
00:30:05,120 --> 00:30:06,735
That should be the cops.

399
00:30:06,788 --> 00:30:09,245
They're probably calling the number on the card.

400
00:30:10,192 --> 00:30:11,705
Answer it.

401
00:30:11,827 --> 00:30:14,115
I'll scream for help.

402
00:30:14,563 --> 00:30:16,315
Darn it.

403
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:20,055
Shouldn't you go?

404
00:30:20,869 --> 00:30:22,855
They're sending officers now.

405
00:30:24,272 --> 00:30:26,200
Do you want to die?

406
00:30:26,208 --> 00:30:29,665
Forget it. Let's go to the office.

407
00:30:32,113 --> 00:30:34,995
Of all the bad luck.

408
00:30:36,284 --> 00:30:37,850
Darn it.

409
00:30:37,853 --> 00:30:41,875
Pay back the rest, got it?

410
00:30:42,591 --> 00:30:44,275
Darn it.

411
00:30:55,370 --> 00:30:58,255
Thanks for your help.

412
00:30:58,740 --> 00:31:00,495
You want to come back...

413
00:31:01,409 --> 00:31:02,865
to our school, right?

414
00:31:04,379 --> 00:31:05,895
I will...

415
00:31:06,514 --> 00:31:08,135
let you.

416
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:12,175
What's your relationship with Su Ah?

417
00:31:13,021 --> 00:31:14,680
Tell me.

418
00:31:14,689 --> 00:31:17,405
Were you really digging into her life?

419
00:31:19,895 --> 00:31:22,990
Does that have anything to do with us?

420
00:31:22,998 --> 00:31:25,755
Don't you just need to be taken care of?

421
00:31:29,571 --> 00:31:33,755
I entered all the entries that were missing in your student records.

422
00:31:33,942 --> 00:31:37,710
I removed the recital because they may ask during the interview.

423
00:31:37,712 --> 00:31:41,065
Everything will go smoothly from now on.

424
00:31:41,850 --> 00:31:43,405
(Han Tae Ra's Academic Schedule)

425
00:31:44,586 --> 00:31:46,075
Fine.

426
00:31:46,621 --> 00:31:51,145
But in exchange, don't mind Su Ah or Han Su.

427
00:31:51,593 --> 00:31:53,045
(Han Tae Ra's Student Record)

428
00:31:53,395 --> 00:31:55,685
Just take good care of my student record.

429
00:31:55,931 --> 00:31:59,955
I don't want things to get awkward with the other kids because of you.

430
00:32:01,102 --> 00:32:04,400
Don't worry. I look forward to working with you.

431
00:32:04,406 --> 00:32:09,095
I will send you to the school that's perfect for you.

432
00:32:14,149 --> 00:32:16,635
(Donghan Hospital)

433
00:32:40,542 --> 00:32:42,565
You said you wanted to know...

434
00:32:43,378 --> 00:32:45,565
how Han Su was doing.

435
00:32:47,916 --> 00:32:49,150
Ma'am.

436
00:32:49,150 --> 00:32:52,375
Let's go in. Han Su's here.

437
00:33:21,549 --> 00:33:23,265
Mr. Gi told me...

438
00:33:24,586 --> 00:33:27,535
that you visited Han Su at the detention center.

439
00:33:28,490 --> 00:33:30,045
How...

440
00:33:31,860 --> 00:33:33,375
Mr. Gi...

441
00:33:34,029 --> 00:33:35,985
is Han Su's attorney.

442
00:33:37,699 --> 00:33:40,855
He came to our school to prove his innocence.

443
00:33:43,838 --> 00:33:46,555
Is it true you visited Han Su?

444
00:33:51,846 --> 00:33:53,295
Byung Ho.

445
00:33:53,748 --> 00:33:56,010
Can you tell me...

446
00:33:56,017 --> 00:33:58,680
what the two of you talked about that day?

447
00:33:58,686 --> 00:34:00,475
I don't know anything.

448
00:34:03,458 --> 00:34:05,375
It isn't your fault.

449
00:34:06,127 --> 00:34:09,015
Whatever you talked about with Han Su,

450
00:34:09,097 --> 00:34:12,355
it wasn't your fault that he attempted suicide.

451
00:34:13,034 --> 00:34:16,700
So don't lower your head like that.

452
00:34:16,704 --> 00:34:19,455
It's someone else who committed the crimes and should be punished.

453
00:34:24,379 --> 00:34:26,335
I brought you here...

454
00:34:26,915 --> 00:34:28,835
for you, Byung Ho.

455
00:34:33,488 --> 00:34:35,505
Ever since Han Su became like this,

456
00:34:36,024 --> 00:34:38,475
it's been hard and torturous for you, too.

457
00:34:39,194 --> 00:34:41,315
I wish you would...

458
00:34:42,797 --> 00:34:45,455
feel at peace.

459
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:50,655
To me, Han Su, Su Ah,

460
00:34:52,006 --> 00:34:53,895
and you...

461
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:57,925
are all equally my precious students.

462
00:35:10,725 --> 00:35:12,545
Please let me be alone...

463
00:35:13,128 --> 00:35:14,575
with Han Su.

464
00:35:15,697 --> 00:35:17,415
I only need a minute.

465
00:35:20,468 --> 00:35:22,115
Please.

466
00:35:24,005 --> 00:35:25,495
Okay.

467
00:35:25,874 --> 00:35:27,355
Got it.

468
00:35:36,084 --> 00:35:42,475
(Patient: Kim Han Su, Nurse in charge: Han Min Jung)

469
00:36:05,847 --> 00:36:07,335
Sorry.

470
00:36:14,589 --> 00:36:16,205
I'm sorry, Han Su.

471
00:36:28,670 --> 00:36:30,155
Who are you?

472
00:36:36,778 --> 00:36:38,725
Who are you? Why do you have Su Ah's picture?

473
00:36:53,928 --> 00:36:55,645
Byung Ho.

474
00:36:56,664 --> 00:36:59,415
Why are you here?

475
00:37:00,868 --> 00:37:02,430
What's this picture?

476
00:37:02,437 --> 00:37:04,330
How's Su Ah? Is she all right?

477
00:37:04,339 --> 00:37:05,970
She can recover, right?

478
00:37:05,974 --> 00:37:07,955
They said it's your fault.

479
00:37:09,544 --> 00:37:11,725
You're responsible for what happened to Su Ah.

480
00:37:11,879 --> 00:37:12,940
What?

481
00:37:12,947 --> 00:37:14,910
If you hadn't meddled in,

482
00:37:14,916 --> 00:37:17,180
Su Ah wouldn't have gotten hurt.

483
00:37:17,185 --> 00:37:20,975
They said it all depends on you...

484
00:37:21,489 --> 00:37:24,450
whether Su Ah will die or recover.

485
00:37:24,459 --> 00:37:27,345
What are you talking about? How does that depend on me?

486
00:37:28,529 --> 00:37:30,185
Do you know...

487
00:37:31,065 --> 00:37:33,055
what happens...

488
00:37:33,067 --> 00:37:36,025
to the Little Mermaid at the end of the tale?

489
00:37:37,438 --> 00:37:39,425
Find it out yourself.

490
00:37:40,775 --> 00:37:43,525
They said the book will let you know how to save Su Ah.

491
00:37:43,678 --> 00:37:46,340
I don't want to do this anymore.

492
00:37:46,347 --> 00:37:49,565
I don't want to have anything to do with you anymore.

493
00:37:49,884 --> 00:37:51,665
Byung Ho, wait!

494
00:37:53,588 --> 00:37:55,105
Who...

495
00:37:55,957 --> 00:37:57,945
Who sent you?

496
00:38:02,797 --> 00:38:05,415
Byung Ho! Byung Ho!

497
00:38:09,037 --> 00:38:10,855
I'm so sorry.

498
00:38:13,908 --> 00:38:16,465
I'm really sorry, Han Su.

499
00:38:20,548 --> 00:38:22,335
It's all my fault.

500
00:38:23,718 --> 00:38:25,265
Han Su.

501
00:38:28,856 --> 00:38:30,345
Han Su.

502
00:38:32,226 --> 00:38:34,075
I'm sorry.

503
00:38:35,463 --> 00:38:37,085
I'm so sorry.

504
00:38:49,377 --> 00:38:51,125
(Patient: Kim Han Su, Nurse in charge: Han Min Jung)

505
00:39:02,557 --> 00:39:04,145
Are you okay?

506
00:39:05,727 --> 00:39:07,275
Yes.

507
00:39:09,497 --> 00:39:11,215
I visited...

508
00:39:12,166 --> 00:39:14,115
Han Su in the prison.

509
00:39:16,337 --> 00:39:18,285
I'll tell you everything...

510
00:39:19,707 --> 00:39:22,095
what we talked about.

511
00:39:27,749 --> 00:39:29,665
You surprised me, my son.

512
00:39:29,817 --> 00:39:32,380
You wanted to have dinner with me.

513
00:39:32,387 --> 00:39:35,120
You're too busy. I don't get to see you much.

514
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:36,520
Now that my exam is over,

515
00:39:36,524 --> 00:39:39,145
I thought we should have dinner together.

516
00:39:39,227 --> 00:39:40,845
All right.

517
00:39:41,129 --> 00:39:44,445
Let's try to spend more time together from now on.

518
00:39:47,835 --> 00:39:49,725
How was your exam?

519
00:39:50,238 --> 00:39:51,700
Wasn't it hard?

520
00:39:51,706 --> 00:39:54,070
It was fine. I think I did well.

521
00:39:54,075 --> 00:39:55,625
I see.

522
00:39:55,943 --> 00:39:58,940
I'm sure you knew the answer to every question.

523
00:39:58,946 --> 00:40:00,510
If you got anything wrong, it must have been a mistake.

524
00:40:00,515 --> 00:40:02,780
I do hope...

525
00:40:02,784 --> 00:40:04,950
you'll come out on top.

526
00:40:04,952 --> 00:40:06,405
Thanks.

527
00:40:13,027 --> 00:40:16,960
I'm thinking of getting out and taking some photos soon.

528
00:40:16,964 --> 00:40:18,490
To get some fresh air.

529
00:40:18,499 --> 00:40:19,500
Photos?

530
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:22,400
Yes. I won a national contest last year...

531
00:40:22,403 --> 00:40:24,230
with some photos I took outdoors.

532
00:40:24,238 --> 00:40:28,140
Do you remember? The prizes were handed out at this hotel.

533
00:40:28,142 --> 00:40:30,540
Of course. I remember that.

534
00:40:30,545 --> 00:40:33,595
It's a shame you couldn't make it.

535
00:40:33,681 --> 00:40:37,165
I really wanted you to be there when I received the prize.

536
00:40:37,318 --> 00:40:39,320
I know.

537
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,950
Too bad I had an important appointment that day.

538
00:40:41,956 --> 00:40:46,545
I would have loved to see my son receive that prize indeed.

539
00:40:57,171 --> 00:40:58,900
How do you feel today?

540
00:40:58,906 --> 00:41:01,395
What is it all of a sudden?

541
00:41:02,243 --> 00:41:04,265
Why is Butler Lee...

542
00:41:22,129 --> 00:41:25,515
By the way, why did Butler Lee do that to you?

543
00:41:28,236 --> 00:41:31,555
How dare he speak to you that way?

544
00:41:31,973 --> 00:41:34,655
You're not letting him get away with it, are you?

545
00:41:34,675 --> 00:41:36,295
Consider it...

546
